<br>
Lots of things can happen while soloing, as many fellow enchanters that have posted here. You can spend almost a full bar of mana locking down a mob that broke charm. (As I've seen a friend Charm solo before) You always loose 50% of the XP, as I highly doubt an enchanter can outdamage a charmed mob. (At higher levels that is) Or things can so drastically wrong, resisted mez's, resisted stuns, ect. ect. and you die.<br>
<br>
And for all of this you get a very very very good pet. Seems balanced to me.<br>
<br>
I don't envy Charm, just another toy for Enchanters to use. <p>Chance is the pseudonym of God when he doesen't want to sign.


