<br>
Charm in itself is not (to me) overpowering, because of the drawback of charm breaking.. any ol' time. Not only that, Enchanter's solo so pisspoor without a pet/charmie (proven enough to me at lower levels) that it's barely worth doing, unless you're bored.<br>
<br>
Which brings me to why people at high levels solo in the first place. Lack of a group! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Me, soloing at this present second, would far rather be in a group and killing more than sitting on my arse and medding for 70% of my time. At least in a group, I'm doing something 80% of the time, instead of able to go AFK for long stretches. Now, being that groups are generally more desireable, if you could, why would you solo? Being that Enchanters are in relative high demand to Magicians, an enchanter solos when they want, not when they must. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52886">Rhasin Firestorm</A><BR>
